message.content:
cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper proposes distributed algorithms for a team of mobile robots to partition and provide coverage of an environment. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper reports on hardware experiments using the Player/Stage robot control system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses a motion protocol and a pairwise partitioning rule to update territory ownership, which can be viewed as control strategies for the robots. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper represents nonconvex environments as graphs and proposes a partitioning and coverage algorithm. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper proposes a distributed algorithm that requires only short-range, unreliable pairwise communication among the robots.
